text.section:
The fiscal court shall adopt a county administrative code which includes, but is not limited to, procedures and designation of responsibility for:
General administration of the office of county judge/executive, county administrative agencies, and public authorities;
Administration of county fiscal affairs, including budget formulation, receipt and disbursement of county funds and preparation of records required for the county audit, and the filing of claims against the county;
Personnel administration, including description and classification of nonelected positions, selection, assignment, supervision and discipline of employees, employee complaints and the county affirmative action program;
County purchasing and award of contracts;
Delivery of county services.
